In the morning before the start, the Hungarians had evolved a strategy to taunt the Russians, whose language they had been forced to study in school. In the words of ZÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¡dor: &quot;We had decided to try and make the Russians angry to distract them.&quot;[2]

